Brilliance is fleeting. 02-Jun-21 03:53 PM
A large, snowy, basin sits here outside of the main resort. This is where all skiers eventually arrive, as the slopes lead here. Ski lifts adorn each of the 3 slopes, with flags and obstacles visible. Interestingly, mountains surround everything, making hopes of escape impossible. The winter snow would freeze anyone who went too far out. This area isn't recognizable by anyone either. Though, focusing on the resort, it looks rather nice. A wooden porch sits along the main entrance, and it has a cozy feel to it. Warming lamps can be found here, as well as ski equipment in case anyone wants to give the slopes a try. Each of the ski lifts leading up to the 3 slopes are marked. The #beginners-slope and the #intermediate-slope take 5 and 7 minutes to each the top, respectively, but the #cliff takes a mere 2. Back to the basin itself. It's largely empty, with a few trees here and there. However, directly in the center of everything, there is a campfire with lamps along the edge of it. Wooden logs surround the fire, so it could be a nice place to gather. But one detail makes this place unsettling. A large monitor sits near the campfire, with a sort of stage near it as well. An image bearing a striking resemblance to Monokuma's eye is hung above the monitor. It doesn't seem you can turn the monitor on, nor will you be able to break it. (edited)

Nine BOT 11-Jul-21 11:42 PM
Nine stood motionless in the snow, simply staring out into empty space. He hadn't moved at all since the motive announcement more than a day prior. Surrounding him were the corpses of his mother and father, his sisters and brothers, but that wasn't what gave him pause. It was the body of the one person who had cared. Despite how much he tried, he found it impossible to move. The darkness around him almost seemed to grow, and he slowly began to feel as though he was getting smaller, weaker. You don't have to keep trying. No one cares about your problems. Only I do. Only 'We' do. An image flickered in his mind. A young malnourished boy, his hair reaching down to his ankles. The boy was sitting in a dark room, facing away from him so that his face wasn't visible. 'I have to focus...its not real. That's not me anymore!' The boy slowly began to turn his head, looking him in the eyes. Long suppressed memories and emotions began surfacing and multiplying, threatening to overwhelm his mind. He had to focus. He desperately reached out for a feeling, anything that wasn't guilt, anxiety, dread. And what he found was anger. "That's right... it's all the bear's fault! It's putting stuff in my head, trying to make me give in! Well I'm not, you hear me!" (edited)
He finally managed to get a grip, snapping back to reality. He stumbled back, falling into the snow. 'Cold...how long have I been out here?' Regardless, he got to his feet, pointing to the sky. "I'm not falling for your illusions, you motherfucker! I stared Death in the face 2 weeks ago, I can handle this!" The words more for himself than for the mastermind, he found that he was full of renewed energy. He had to focus on the anger, use it to anchor himself. As he began moving, even in the back of his mind he recognized that the solution was only temporary. It was like a plumber putting duct tape over a broken pipe. But for now, it was good enough. Even still, the voice resounded, taunting him. You can't keep running away from us, XXXX.
